<h2>Conditional methods on observations</h2>
<p>
   Conditioning uncertainty on data is the process of refining a model structure, or a distribution of parameter
   values of a model structure as more data become available. A modeller needs to decide on:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Sampling methods</li>
  <li>Evaluation methods</li>
  <li>If possible gives some context on your choices or assumptions you made for these choices.</li>
  <li>Pathway Parameters</li>
  <li>Receptor/Consequence model</li>
  <li>Joint Hazards</li>
  <li>Model Validation / Conditioning Data</li>
</ul>  

<p>We follow the source-pathway-receptor framework but a modeller might choose to construct his own workflow.</p>
</body>
